<br>
1. Special NPCs, ala the Priests of Discord, that could give you the option of changing your alignment, on a one time only basis, and only for the purposes of becoming a renegade/outcast member of your society.  Yes, this would allow the good dark elven necromancers...but bear with me.<br>
<br>
2. For each category (class, race, and god) you were out-of-step, the internal conflict made it harder for you to learn, the act of gaining experience would be more difficult since so much of your mental energy would be devoted to breaking with your intrinsic nature and ingrained culture and habits.  +5% required to earned experience at each level for each violation (so good dark elven necromancers would take a +30% xp penalty +5% neutral, +5% each for good for race, class, and diety.)<br>
<br>
3. For each category (class, race, and god) you go out-of-step with, you automatically take a 1 step faction hit with all factions of your home city.  The aforementioned dark elf would be solidly KOS (-6 levels of faction loss, since scowling is -4 levels from indifferant, the best they could ever hope to regain is dubious.)  There would be no faction benefit with any other factions in game though.<br>
<br>
4. Certain quests can be defined as &quot;good&quot; and others &quot;evil.&quot;  Some can be defined as neutral obviously.  Similar for killing creatures.  All factions can be assigned good and evil.  Getting +faction with a good faction should include a small +good and -evil adjustment, and vice versa for evil.  In this way, the person who plays counter to alignment and does evil when they should do good, or good when they should do evil, would start suffering in-game social consequences.  If you are evil, your evil faction can affect how evil NPCs react to you, but good faction is ignored.  If neutral, neither good nor evil faction would matter.  If good, the reverse of evil would apply.<br>
<br>
5. Casting spells on those of opposite alignment, grouping outside your alignment, and so on, should incur a good/evil faction hit as appropriate.  Grouping with differing alignments (even good/neutral or neutral/evil) should incur a penalty to earned xp as before.  Introduce a /con system so that people can know perhaps, or a level 1 spell common to all casters (and hybrids at level 9) called &quot;know alignment&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If you are foolish enough to bless evil as good (or vice versa) you deserve the hit. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=425651">Kypin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
